==English==
===Etymology===
 Modern Latin, from Greek [[στεατο-]] (denoting fatty tissue, from [[στεαρ]] ‘fat, tallow, suet’) + [[πυγη]] ‘rump’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /stɪə'tɒpɪgəs/

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|steatopygous}}
# pertaining to [[steatopygia]]; having [[fat]] or prominent [[buttocks]]
#:*'''1963''': Perhaps, he now felt, if this body he held could become – just for twenty or thirty seconds – one of those harem dreams of his, pampered, pouting, perfumed, '''steatopygous''', he could, he was sure, achieve what it was a plain duty, apart from all questions of gratification, to achieve. — Anthony Burgess, ''Inside Mr. Enderby''